{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed0fb5d8-73f2-4284-925e-6f12ac3e54b7","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Scenario | Events |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created → Activated` |\n| Backgrounded | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| Returned to foreground | `Resumed → Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst only — use it to save state before the OS may terminate your app. On Android/Windows it won't fire.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c40d5c00-0844-45fe-8db3-41aae6a22f32","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development - I can answer this directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":420,"requestId":"A43C:1FA0A7:5CD59C6:6553B33:69F004DF"},"id":"828f0db4-224f-48ae-9de0-3225c7d6da0a","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:52:56.935Z","parentId":"fbcb7e8a-5b89-4200-b4f3-9ba91287dcb1"}
